-- China Says Singapore Should Safeguard Rights of Chinese Workers
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-11-30T07:23:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-30/china-says-singapore-should-safeguard-rights-of-chinese-workers.html
Chinese foreign ministry spokesman
Hong Lei said Singapore should “earnestly safeguard” the
lawful rights of Chinese workers arrested for their role in
labor protests.  Singapore should deal with the sitution in a prudent
manner, Hong said today at a regular breifing in Beijing. Four
Chinese citizens were charged in a court yesterday with
instigating SMRT Corp. bus drivers to take part in an illegal
strike this week, according to court filings.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
Nicholas Wadhams in Beijing at 
